			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Epic Update<a name="51425"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 1:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
Okay, I read so many horror stories about camps here that I thought I'd share some of my recent experiences.  
<br />

<br />
So a while ago I got my red and white dragon scales in the bazaar for a reasonable price (for Stromm).  So this past Thursday I decided to start my epic finally.  I went and did the running around part which was easy.  Then I killed Maligar (who was up when I got to camp).  Not really knowing how hard he was I brought 3 other lvl 65 people with me.  Lol.  Oops, didn't need them.  Then I went to the Ocean of Tears to camp the cyclops.  After about an hour and a half of killing cyclops, he never spawned.  
<br />

<br />
So I give up and go to bed.  Friday I wake up and go back there.  In 10 minutes he spawns and I get my horn.  Cool.  Go do the turn in and get my note.  Now, having my scales already I go do the turn in to get the lute body.  
<br />

<br />
NOTE:  DO NOT hand in the note with the scales turn in!!  The note to Fropar MUST BE turned in with the lute neck pieces.  More on that later.  
<br />

<br />
I turn in the scales AND the note to fropar.  Get the lute body and he keeps the note.  Here's where it gets fun.  I go to Rathe Mountains and in ten minutes get the named to spawn and loot my guts.  I go to Burning Woods and look around solo.  I highsun several mobs and wander around the spot to see if I get the PH.  Lo and behold I get him after 30 minutes.  So I camp the PH's.  Get the wrong named to spawn and kill him.  Then I get the correct named to spawn but the bugger summons.  Try to chant kite him, no good.  Try to throw charmed mobs at him, no good.  Melee'd him (while I had help on the way) and he had me to 80% while he was at 96%.  Mez him in place and a 55 wizard and my wife's 65 beast show up.  He goes down in 30 seconds.  Amazingly easy!
<br />

<br />
THEN I go with my wife to Skyfire since we're so close and OMG Eldrig was up on TRACK!!  Woot!!  We run over and smoke him.  BAM 3 guts and page 25 is mine!  
<br />

<br />
With this amazing luck I figure to keep going.  I watch the auction channel and someone working on their monk epic in Karanor's.  They say they've got a skull rotting.  I send a tell and I'm off to Karanor's.  I get there and have to get routed in since I've never actually been there.  I'm 30 seconds late and the skull rotted.  d*mn.  So I sit there for 20 minutes bullsh*tting with the guy working it.  The very next warlord that popped had another skull.  WOW, what luck again!!  I looted it and BS'd some more.  Turns out the same guy had a kedge backbone he'd looted earlier that day working his mage epic.  He's very nice and we sort of agree that he might MQ it for me if I get my fear whip soon.
<br />

<br />
Skip ahead to Saturday.  Saturday afternoon I get an 8 person group together and go to PoFear.  The very first Amalgyn Warrior that dies drops the Amy Whip.  I snag that and send a tell to the mage.  We agree on 5k (he'd probably have given it for free but I'd have felt guilty) and we go do the turn in.
<br />

<br />
Here's the only bad part.  Look back up and see I had already turned my note to Fropar in.  I thought you only had to turn it in once.  We do the MQ and Fropar eats all 3 items.  OMG I was really sad.  However since I'd been so lucky I decided to not cry like a school girl.  I go back to OOT and within 5-15 minutes get lucky and get another named cylops to pop.  Kill him, get my horn (again).  I run back and get another note to Fropar.  Now till that point my plan had been to /petition and try to get the items back.  On a sudden inspiration I run over to Steamfont and just turn the note in solo.  It was maybe 30 minutes after I had lost all 3 items to Fropar.  Holy crap he gave me my lute neck!!!  It counted it as still one whole MQ and no one had messed with him between visits.  Lol.
<br />

<br />
So now I have (Starting Thr running through Saturday) both page 24 top and bottom, page 25, lute neck, and lute body.  In 3 days.  AND a bard friend of mine tells me that UDB is up in Old Seb!!!!  That Saturday night!  I could have finished my epic in 3 days time, start to finish, but he had been waiting for UDB for a lot longer than I had.  So I went with him and his guild to help him out.  He got the trak guts.  I was happy for him.  
<br />

<br />
Soon though, the next or the one after, UDB will be mine and I'll have my epic!!  I could not believe the string of luck I had in either camping, buying, or MQ'ing all of the epic in 3 days except for Trak.  And if I'd been a bastard (and it crossed my mind.....lol) I could have had the UDB and actually completed my epic in 3 days.  d*mn that conscience!!!
<br />

<br />
Just thought I'd share a positive not on epics since there are so many bad ones about long camp times.  On occassion, you get really really lucky!!
<br />

<br />
Good hunting on yours!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
